post.description:
To update the avatar, define image URL in 'avatar' field. like 

```javascript
{
	'avatar': 'URL_HERE'
}
```

Below is an example of the body parameter

	{
		"blocks":[
			{
				"type": "text",
				"value": "This is <b>bold</b>, <i>italic</i>, and <b><i>bold+italic</i></b>"
			},
			{
				"type": "text",
				"value": "<link type="manager" value="managerId_goes_here">@username</link>"
			},
			{
				"type": "text",
				"value": "This is a url <link type="url" value="https://channel.io">https://channel.io</link>"
			},
			{
				"type": "text",
				"value": "This is a link <link type="url" value="https://channel.io">Channel</link>"
			},
			{
				"type": "code",
				"value": "<script>ChannelIO('boot')</script>"
			},
			{
				"type": "bullets",
				"blocks":[
					{
						"type": "text"
						"value": "Bulleted text goes here"
					},
					{
						"type": "text"
						"value": "Next bulleted text goes here"
					}
				]
			}
		],
		"options": [
			"actAsManager", "doNotPost", "doNotSearch", "doNotSendApp", "immutable", "private", "silent"
			],
		}
	}

Parameter descriptions

blocks: Every message is wrapped in `blocks`. As seen as the example above, each `block` has a `type` and a `value`.
There are 3 types of `type`. `text` is for plain text. `code` is for code blocks. `bullets` is for bulleted text.
Formatting of the texts can be used as the example above

`options`: Set of message options. There are 7 available options and can be used together

`option.actAsManager`: If included in `options`, the message behaves as if a manager has sent it

`option.doNotPost`: If included in `options`, the message is not sent to follow-up messages(text message / email)

`option.doNotSearch`: If included in `options`, the message cannot be searched

`option.doNotSendApp`: If included in `options`, the message is not sent to external messenger apps

`option.immutable`: If included in `options`, the message cannot be deleted, or modified

`option.private`: If included in `options`, the message is private, and can only be seen to managers

`option.silent`: If included in `options`, the message does not send notifications unless it's an important message

Below is an example of the body parameter

	{
		"blocks":[
			{
				"type": "text",
				"value": "This is <b>bold</b>, <i>italic</i>, and <b><i>bold+italic</i></b>"
			},
			{
				"type": "text",
				"value": "<link type="manager" value="managerId_goes_here">@username</link>"
			},
			{
				"type": "text",
